data.chText: 影响；作用
data.enText: the effect that sb/sth has on the way a person thinks or behaves or on the way that sth works or develops

data.chText: 对某人产生强大的影响
data.enText: to have/exert a strong influence on sb

data.chText: 气候对农业生产的影响
data.enText: the influence of the climate on agricultural production

data.chText: 电视对儿童究竟有什么影响？
data.enText: What exactly is the influence of television on children?

data.chText: 支配力；控制力；影响力
data.enText: the power that sb/sth has to make sb/sth behave in a particular way

data.chText: 她的父母对她不再有任何真正的影响力了。
data.enText: Her parents no longer have any real influence over her.

data.chText: 她很有可能对经理施展她的影响力，给你弄份工作。
data.enText: She could probably exert her influence with the manager and get you a job.

data.chText: 他是在吸毒后犯罪的。
data.enText: He committed the crime under the influence of drugs.

data.chText: 有影响的人（或事物）
data.enText: a person or thing that affects the way a person behaves and thinks

data.chText: 文化影响
data.enText: cultural influences

data.chText: 那些朋友对她有负面的影响。
data.enText: Those friends are a bad influence on her.

data.chText: 他的第一位音乐老师是他一生中对他影响非常大的人。
data.enText: His first music teacher was a major influence in his life.
under the influence

data.chText: 喝酒过多；醉酒
data.enText: having had too much alcohol to drink

data.chText: 她被控酒后驾驶。
data.enText: She was charged with driving under the influence.

data.chText: 影响；对…起作用
data.enText: to have an effect on the way that sb behaves or thinks, especially by giving them an example to follow

data.chText: 他的作品影响了千百万人。
data.enText: His writings have influenced the lives of millions.

data.chText: 受到某事物的强烈影响
data.enText: to be strongly influenced by sth

data.chText: 何去何从都别受我的影响。
data.enText: Don't let me influence you either way.

data.chText: 问题的措辞会影响人们的回答。
data.enText: The wording of questions can influence how people answer.

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.chText: 支配；左右
data.enText: to have an effect on a particular situation and the way that it develops

data.chText: 诸多社会因素左右着人的预期寿命。
data.enText: A number of social factors influence life expectancy.

simple_means.memory_skill: in 进入 + flu 流动 + ence 表行为 → 流入 → 影响

ex.chText: 食物是为受洪水影响的地区准备的。
ex.enText: The food is for the areas affected by the flood.

synonyms.bx: 通常由物作主语，多产生消极作用。

ex.chText: 他那天的讲座让听众印象尤深。
ex.enText: His lecture that day impressed the audience.

ex.chText: 长城给我留下了深刻印象。
ex.enText: The Great Wall impressed me the most.

synonyms.bx: 指给人留下很深的印象，从而受到影响和感动，比 affect 影响更深，时间更长。

ex.chText: 是什么影响他去从事教学工作？
ex.enText: What influenced him to take up teaching?

synonyms.bx: 通常指潜移默化地起作用。

ex.zh: 产生良好/不好影响的人（或事物）

data.enText: under the influence

data.chText: 喝酒过多；醉酒
data.enText: having had too much alcohol to drink

data.chText: 她被控酒后驾驶。
data.enText: She was charged with driving under the influence.

tr: causing something without any direct or apparent effort
a power to affect persons or events especially power based on prestige etc
example: used her parents' influence to get the job

tr: a cognitive factor that tends to have an effect on what you do
example: her wishes had a great influence on his thinking

tr: one having power to influence another
example: she was the most important influence in my life
he was a bad influence on the children

tr: the effect of one thing (or person) on another
induce into action by using one's charm
example: She charmed him into giving her all his money

tr: have and exert influence or effect
example: The artist's work influenced the young painter
She worked on her friends to support the political candidate

value.def: Influence is the power to make other people agree with your opinions or do what you want.

example.ex: As Hugh grew older, she had less influence and couldn't control him...
example.tran: 休慢慢长大,她的影响力变小了,无法再控制他了。

example.ex: I have rather a large influence over a good many people...
example.tran: 我对很多人都有相当大的影响力。

example.ex: He denies exerting any political influence over them...
example.tran: 他否认对他们施加了任何政治压力。

example.ex: The government should continue to use its influence for the release of all hostages.
example.tran: 政府应继续运用其影响力来解救所有人质。

value.tran: 势力;权势;影响力;支配力

value.def: If you influence someone, you use your power to make them agree with you or do what you want.

example.ex: He is trying to improperly influence a witness...
example.tran: 他在试图误导证人。

example.ex: The angry crowds could influence the government...
example.tran: 愤怒的群众可以影响政府。

example.ex: My dad influenced me to do electronics.
example.tran: 我学电子是受爸爸的影响。

value.def: To have an influence on people or situations means to affect what they do or what happens.

example.ex: Van Gogh had a major influence on the development of modern painting...
example.tran: 凡·高对现代绘画的发展有着重大影响。

example.ex: The Shropshire landscape was an influence on Owen too...
example.tran: 什罗普郡的风景也对欧文产生了影响。

example.ex: Many other medications have an influence on cholesterol levels.
example.tran: 许多其他的药物治疗对胆固醇水平都有一定的影响。

value.def: If someone or something influences a person or situation, they have an effect on that person's behaviour or that situation.

example.ex: We became the best of friends and he influenced me deeply...
example.tran: 我们成了最好的朋友,他深深地影响了我。

example.ex: What you eat may influence your risk of getting cancer...
example.tran: 你吃的东西会影响你患癌症的风险。

example.ex: They still influence what's played on the radio.
example.tran: 他们对电台播放什么节目仍然会有影响。

value.def: Someone or something that is a good or bad influence on people has a good or bad effect on them.

example.ex: I thought Sue would be a good influence on you...
example.tran: 我认为苏能对你产生良好影响。

example.ex: TV is a bad influence on people.
example.tran: 电视会对人们产生不良影响。

gramarinfo.label: usu sing, usu adj N, oft N <l>on</l> n

value.def: If you are under the influence of someone or something, you are being affected or controlled by them.

example.ex: I fell under the influence of a history master...
example.tran: 我当时深受一位历史老师的影响。

example.ex: The very earliest sculptures were made under the influence of Greek art...
example.tran: 最早的雕塑作品受到了希腊艺术的影响。

example.ex: He was arrested on suspicion of driving under the influence of alcohol.
example.tran: 他因涉嫌酒后驾驶被捕。

gramarinfo.label: PHR n, usu v-link PHR, PHR after v

value.tran: 在…影响之下;在…控制之下

value.def: If someone is under the influence, their mind is affected by alcohol or drugs.

example.ex: Police charged the man with driving under the influence...
example.tran: 警方指控那名男子酒后驾车。

example.ex: We find members of the opposite sex more attractive when under the influence.
example.tran: 我们喝醉时感到异性更具吸引力。

value.tran: 喝醉;(吸食毒品后)处于迷幻状态

trans: 产生良好/不好影响的人（或事物）

con 共同 + flu 流动 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 流到一起 → 汇流的
ef 出 + flu 流动 + ent 表物 → 流出物
ef〔= e 出〕+ fluv〔= flu〕流动 + ial …的 → 流出〔不好的〕气味 → 恶臭的
flu 流动 + ency 表状态 → 流的状态 → 流畅
fluid 流动的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 流动性
flu 流动 + sh → 奔流；冲洗
in 进入 + flu 流动 + ence 表行为 → 流入 → 影响
in 进入 + flu 流动 + enza 病 → 流行病 → 流行感冒
in 进入 + flux 流动 → 流入 → 涌入
melli 蜂蜜 + flu 流动 + ous …的 → 流出蜂蜜 → 甜美的
re 回 + flu 流动 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 流回去 → 倒流的
super 过多 + flu 流动 + ous 有…性质的，关于…的 → 多流出来的 → 过剩的
